# .cursorrules — MIRA (Cursor reads this on every request)
# Mirror of CLAUDE.md. If this and CLAUDE.md ever conflict, CLAUDE.md wins.

PROJECT
MIRA = a web app: student types a scenario -> rehearses a spoken conversation with a 3D
virtual client (React Three Fiber) -> gets an AI communication coaching report.
Rank-#1 hackathon target. Reliability and polish over feature count.

PRIME DIRECTIVES (never violate)
- Contracts before code: src/types.ts shapes are FROZEN. Don't change a shape unless told.
- Walking skeleton first: whole flow must click on MOCK data before any real cloud call.
- Everything mockable: every AWS/external call behind a service with Mock+Real, switched by USE_MOCKS.
- Small diffs that always compile. Prefer editing over regenerating files. Never break the build.
- No new npm dependencies without asking. When unsure, ASK — never invent APIs, params, or model names.

STACK (pinned — do not substitute)
- Next.js App Router + TypeScript strict + Tailwind + shadcn/ui. No other UI kit.
- 3D: React Three Fiber + drei (not raw three.js in components).
- VERSION PAIRING (prevents #1 install error):
    React 19 / Next 15 -> @react-three/fiber@^9 + @react-three/drei@^10
    React 18 / Next 14 -> @react-three/fiber@^8 + @react-three/drei@^9
  Check the installed react version FIRST, then match the R3F/drei major. Let npm resolve three.
- State: React hooks + a single useSession() context. No Redux/Zustand unless asked.

ARCHITECTURE
- Client never holds AWS keys or imports a service. Only app/api/* routes call services.
- Each /api route accepts ?demo=1 -> returns a fixture from src/fixtures/ no matter what.
- Wire real services priority: Bedrock -> Polly -> Transcribe. Comprehend/Rekognition last.
- If a service is risky, keep it mocked and say so in UI/pitch. Never fake an AWS claim.

GOING LIVE ON AWS (USE_MOCKS=false) — full runbook in docs/AWS_SETUP.md
- Stack: Bedrock (@aws-sdk/client-bedrock-runtime) persona/dialogue/report; Polly
  (@aws-sdk/client-polly) voice; Transcribe (optional) STT; S3 (optional) recordings. Region us-east-1.
- Process: request Bedrock model access -> IAM user + key -> cp .env.example .env.local,
  set keys + USE_MOCKS=false + BEDROCK_MODEL_ID -> npm i SDK -> implement real* stubs in services/* -> verify per tier.
- lib/metrics.ts owns the numbers even in real mode; Claude writes only the prose.

KNOWN GAP (top priority)
- mockParseScenario ignores its input and always returns one persona. Build a KEYWORD ROUTER
  (medical / IT-client / difficult-conversation -> distinct personas) so "scenario drives the
  environment" is TRUE on mocks. Highest-value open task.

THREE.JS / R3F (interactive AND safe)
- Build the avatar PROCEDURALLY from primitives. NO external .gltf/.glb assets (zero load risk).
- 3D files start with 'use client'; AvatarStage imported via dynamic(import, { ssr:false }). Three.js can't SSR.
- One <Canvas> for the room: dpr={[1,2]}, shadows, camera position ~[0,1.4,4] fov 45.
- Lighting encodes mood + adds polish: ambient + 1 directional (shadow) + colored rim
    (anxious=amber, angry=red, sad=blue, neutral=teal).
- Animate ONLY via useFrame: idle breathing always; stronger 'talk' motion gated by `speaking`.
- Mood changes posture + material color. NO lip-sync (time-sink trap).
- drei polish allowed: ContactShadows, Environment, Float (subtle), OrbitControls (no zoom/pan).
- Frozen component contract: <AvatarStage persona mood speaking />. DOM (camera self-view, transcript) layers around the Canvas.
- 3D only where it earns attention (the persona/room). Keep forms and the report as crisp DOM.

CODE STYLE
- strict TS, no any (use unknown + narrow). Components < ~150 lines, single responsibility.
- Tailwind layout + shadcn primitives. Tokens: navy #1b2a3a, teal #0fb5ae, AWS orange #ff9900.
- Keyboard-accessible, captions on by default, focus rings, loading/empty states everywhere.

WORKFLOW (every task)
1) Plan first: restate task, list files to touch, name the types. Wait for go.
2) Implement the smallest slice that compiles. Don't touch unrelated files.
3) Verify: build + typecheck; fix errors with the smallest change; screenshot UI changes.
4) Report what changed + the next smallest step.
- For lib/metrics.ts (talkRatio, fillers, wpm, open/closed) WRITE TESTS FIRST.

ANTI-PATTERNS (do not do)
- Regenerating whole working files. Changing a types.ts shape or API field name unasked.
- External 3D models, lip-sync, or avatar polish before the Report screen works.
- AWS SDK/keys in client components. Any change leaving npm run build failing.
